Lachlan Keith Murdoch (/ˈlɒklən ˈmɜːrdɒk/;[4] born 8 September 1971) is an American businessman and mass media heir.[3][5] He is the executive chairman of Nova Entertainment, executive co-chairman of News Corp and 21st Century Fox, the founder of Australian investment company Illyria Pty Ltd, and a director of Sydney's Museum of Contemporary Art.



